newsitem.title: CHINA: Shanghai soybean ends mixed in slow trading.
newsitem.headline: Shanghai soybean ends mixed in slow trading.

text.p: Shanghai soybean futures ended mixed in slow trading on Thursday as the market remained unclear about short term direction, traders said.
The key March 1997 contract opened at 3,155 yuan, falling five yuan from Wednesday, and stayed at that level throughout the day.
May rose 66 to 3,266, July fell five to 3,275, Setember three to 3,375, November 10 to 3,390, and the January 1998 contract increased nine to 3,410.
Combined volume was unchanged at 17,700 tonnes.
Traders said lack of trading interest left only retail investors in the market.
"Most investors have left the soybean market because of the upcoming Chinese New Year holiday" one trader said. China's premier annual vacation begins on February 6.
Most traders said they believed soybean prices would continue to move in a narrow range in the short term.
